<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Winchester" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Winchester;</orth> Henry Beaufort Bishop of W.: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 19</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.118" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 64</bibl>. 107 etc. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 28</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.120" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 56</bibl> Gardiner, Bishop of W.: <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.231" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 2, 231</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.101" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 101</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 58</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 58</bibl><lb /><emph>W. goose,</emph> cant term for a certain venereal sore, thought to have originated from the public stews in Southwark being under the jurisdiction of the Bishop of Winchester: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 55</bibl>.
